{"id": "EUVD-2017-9625", "enisaUuid": "595358ef-9487-3692-b775-fbb85e273b9b", "description": "An issue was discovered in net/ipv6/ip6mr.c in the Linux kernel before 4.11. By setting a specific socket option, an attacker can control a pointer in kernel land and cause an inet_csk_listen_stop general protection fault, or potentially execute arbitrary code under certain circumstances. The issue can be triggered as root (e.g., inside a default LXC container or with the CAP_NET_ADMIN capability) or after namespace unsharing. This occurs because sk_type and protocol are not checked in the appropriate part of the ip6_mroute_* functions. NOTE: this affects Linux distributions that use 4.9.x longterm kernels before 4.9.187.", "datePublished": "2019-08-13T13:17:36", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-05T21:28:54", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2017-18509.html", "https://www.debian.org/security/2019/dsa-4497", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2017-18509", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2017-18509.html", "https://pulsesecurity.co.nz/advisories/linux-kernel-4.9-inetcsklistenstop-gpf", "https://salsa.debian.org/kernel-team/linux/commit/baefcdc2f29923e7325ce4e1a72c3ff0a9800f32", "https://lists.openwall.net/netdev/2017/12/04/40", "https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/99253eb750fda6a644d5188fb26c43bad8d5a745", "https://git.kernel.org/cgit/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/commit/?id=99253eb750fda6a644d5188fb26c43bad8d5a745", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2019/08/msg00016.html", "https://seclists.org/bugtraq/2019/Aug/26", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2019/08/msg00017.html", "http://packetstormsecurity.com/files/154059/Slackware-Security-Advisory-Slackware-14.2-kernel-Updates.html", "https://support.f5.com/csp/article/K41582535", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/4145-1/", "https://support.f5.com/csp/article/K41582535?utm_source=f5